Package dev.lazurite.thimble.synchronizer.key

Class SynchronizedKey<T>

java.lang.Object
dev.lazurite.thimble.synchronizer.key.SynchronizedKey<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of the key
public class SynchronizedKey<T>
extends java.lang.Object
A SynchronizedKey object represents the name of a synchronized value to be synced across the network. It doesn't actually contain the value, but serves as a way for the Synchronizer to reference it.

  • Constructor Details

    • SynchronizedKey

      public SynchronizedKey​(net.minecraft.util.Identifier identifier, SynchronizedType<T> type, T fallback)
      Basic constructor that passes in all the necessary key information.
      Parameters:
      identifier - the Identifier used for recognizing the key when read from disk or a packet
      type - the type of the key
      fallback - the fallback value of the key in case the value is not initialized

    • SynchronizedKey

      public SynchronizedKey​(net.minecraft.util.Identifier identifier, SynchronizedType<T> type, T fallback, java.util.function.Consumer<T> consumer)
      Another basic constructor that passes all the necessary information in addition to a Consumer object. The purpose of the Consumer is to allow you to execute custom code whenever the synchronized value is changed.
      Parameters:
      identifier - the Identifier used for recognizing the key when read from disk or a packet
      type - the type of the key
      fallback - the fallback value of the key in case the value is not initialized
      consumer - the Consumer which is executed any time the value is changed
